  "prompt": "How do you clean a remote control?",
  "response": "Here's how to clean a remote control:\n\n1. Remove batteries first\n\n2. Basic cleaning:\n- Use a soft, slightly damp cloth to wipe the surface\n- Pay special attention to buttons and crevices\n- Don't use too much moisture\n\n3. Disinfecting:\n- Use disinfectant wipes or a cloth with rubbing alcohol\n- Don't saturate the remote\n- Gently clean all surfaces and between buttons\n\n4. Deep cleaning:\n- Use a cotton swab with rubbing alcohol for hard-to-reach areas\n- Carefully clean between buttons\n- Use a toothpick to remove debris from tight spaces\n\n5. Drying:\n- Let the remote air dry completely\n- Ensure no moisture remains before reinserting batteries\n\n6. Additional tips:\n- Clean regularly to prevent grime buildup\n- Be gentle to avoid damaging buttons\n- Never submerge the remote in liquid\n- Use compressed air to blow out dust and debris\n\n7. For stubborn dirt:\n- Use a slightly damp cloth with mild soap\n- Dry thoroughly afterward\n\nRemember to be gentle and avoid excessive moisture during cleaning.",
